## Rise at Seven — Best for Creative Link Earning

**Based in:** Sheffield, with London and US offices

[Rise at Seven](https://riseatse7en.com) built their reputation on creative-led SEO — campaigns designed to earn links through digital PR, data journalism, and content that genuinely gets covered in national press. They have produced campaigns for major UK brands and demonstrated organic link acquisition at scale through newsjacking, data-led reports, and creative concepts that attract coverage without outreach spam.

**Best for:** Consumer brands, e-commerce businesses, and companies in industries where editorial coverage in mainstream media is achievable. Works well for businesses willing to invest in campaign-style content rather than incremental content production.

**Strengths:**
- Strong track record of link acquisition through earned media rather than purchased placements
- Creative team that understands both journalism and search — a rare combination
- Publicly shared case studies with verifiable traffic data

**Considerations:**
- Creative-led approach requires client involvement and approval cycles for campaign concepts
- Less suited to B2B, technical, or regulated industries where editorial coverage is harder to achieve
- Pricing typically starts at £3,000-£6,000/month

---

## Aira — Best for Data-Driven Digital PR

**Based in:** Northampton (remote-first)

[Aira](https://aira.net) specialises in the intersection of digital PR and SEO, with a team known for publishing research-backed campaigns that attract links from high-authority publications. They have produced transparent reports on their own methodology, including honest post-mortems on campaigns that underperformed. That transparency is unusual in an industry where agencies routinely hide failures.

**Best for:** Businesses wanting to build domain authority through earned links alongside on-page SEO. Particularly strong for mid-market companies in competitive verticals where authority is the differentiating factor.

**Strengths:**
- Honest, data-driven culture — publishes internal research including failure analysis
- Strong understanding of both the SEO and PR disciplines
- Good track record in content-led link acquisition

**Considerations:**
- Like most digital PR agencies, success depends partly on media climate and newsworthiness
- Less focus on semantic content architecture compared to methodology-first specialists

